The things I learned this week

I learned basic stats

For example, t-test

# import data
GardenOzone <- read.csv("Data/GardenOzone.csv")

# t-test
t.test(Ozone ~ Garden.location, data = GardenOzone)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Ozone by Garden.location
## t = 4.2363, df = 17.656, p-value = 0.0005159
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group East and group West is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##   8.094171 24.065829
## sample estimates:
## mean in group East mean in group West 
##              77.34              61.26

I learned how to plot

library(ggplot2)
daphnia <- read.csv("Data/Daphniagrowth.csv")
